                "part_metadata": null,
                "text": "Alba Cristina Magalhães Alves de Melo's academic and professional background aligns strongly with the project. Her research interests explicitly include High Performance Computing, Accelerators (GPU, FPGA), and Bioinformatics.\n\nHer lines of research directly support the project's themes:\n*   \"Programação com Memória Compartilhada e Troca de Mensagens em Clusters de Computadores\" (Parallel Programming on Clusters).\n*   \"Computação em Ambientes Heterogêneos para Aplicações de Bioinformática\" (Heterogeneous Computing for Bioinformatics Applications), which investigates using heterogeneous environments, grid computing, reconfigurable hardware, and GPUs for bioinformatics.\n\nAcademically, her PhD and Master's focused on parallel systems, distributed shared memory, and parallel process management. Professionally, she is a Full Professor in Computer Science, Vice-chair of the IEEE Technical Committee in Parallel Processing, and a Member of the Brazilian Delegation for the BRICS Working Group on High Performance Computing and Information and Communication Technologies. She also serves as an Associate Editor for several prominent journals in parallel and distributed computing.",
